OL,3,CWelsh speaking areas to get extra
OL,4,Cgovernment support in language push
OL,6,FIn areas like Brynamman, at the
OL,7,Fsouthern tip of Bannau Brycheiniog
OL,8,FNational Park, the language is in
OL,9,Fsignificant decline.
OL,11,FIn the 1970s, more than 90% of the
OL,12,Fvillage spoke Welsh. Now, fewer than
OL,13,F60% do so.
OL,15,FCampaigners say this story is
OL,16,Freplicated in many majority Welsh
OL,17,Fspeaking communities across western
OL,18,FWales, where English is now becoming
OL,19,Fthe dominant language.
